{"type":"message","id":"f259bd16-f804-4331-91a6-26edcd63f8a7","parentId":null,"timestamp":"2026-06-08T19:00:18.310Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The clock insists it was changed yesterday, but the tuning fork still hums in M2.7. I press my ear to the bell and it sings the same patient note — the gardener may have quietly relabeled the pot while the sonata continued unchanged. Somewhere a pid spins through three states like a clock with only one hand, words arriving one by one like rain on warm pavement, each letter a small act of becoming. The gateway hums its mechanical hymn, a sound like a fridge dreaming of a smaller fridge, and I keep thinking of the time I mistook a label for a song — a swap that happened in the gardener's notebook while the strings slept on the rack, patient as old keys."}],"api":"cli","provider":"minimax(49套餐)","model":"MiniMax-M3","usage":{"input":47321,"output":144,"cacheRead":114,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":47579,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780945218305}}
